cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of the satisfiability problem for a two-variable first-order logic on trees. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with vector addition systems with a stack. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with reachability in a formal language model. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of a problem in a programming language model. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of a computational problem.
